Computers are a symbol of modern times, but surprisingly, more than 2000 years ago, ancient Greeks already manufactured real computing machines.
In III century BC three of the most important human inventions appeared: Ctesibius' clock, Heron's hodometer, and the incredible Antikythera mechanism, whose functions are still under investigation by researchers.
These instruments deeply influenced the progress of technology in the following centuries. They weren't isolated cases, but they appeared in a time of extraordinary progresses in many knowledge fields, and in which the basis of modern science was laid down.

